   "source": [
    "#preprocessing\n",
    "#fix the missing value\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "print(df.isnull().sum().sum(), \"missing values remaining\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "39bad529-083d-41bd-86bb-a56834fcb1af",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "0 missing value here"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "641217e2-ac1f-40dd-8e86-b7eae7b1f836",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "6033916b-26d7-483d-b8f4-05bec3a4fe98",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#binarise the target\n",
    "df['target'] = (df['target'] > 0).astype(int)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1a6c14ef-1494-4c24-af75-5ada9c158c31",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The original \"target\" column has values from 0-4 and 0 being healthy and 1 to 4 showing the stage of heart disease."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "2f35fcb4-8c11-4220-8872-94809b0cd1f4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#encode categorical columns\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "df = pd.get_dummies(df, columns=['cp', 'restecg', 'slope', 'ca', 'thal'], drop_first=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5257a59c-9572-424d-9145-026b4ac9885b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "One-hot encoding converts categorical columns like cp and thal into separate yes/no columns, so the model does not assume higher numbers are more important. drop_first=True removes one column per feature to avoid confusing the Logistic Regression model with duplicate information."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "af4b8684-aca0-4ccd-ae7e-c0b9ab948504",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#split features and target\n",
    "X = df.drop('target', axis=1)\n",
    "y = df['target']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cfd5c728-b5d8-4d44-8fe7-5395e4b30587",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "x is the input ,y is the target ,which will be the output"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "158e2df1-e000-4f14-8def-26ac2eff6907",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Training samples : 820\n",
      "Testing  samples : 205\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "#train/test and split scaling\n",
    "X_train_raw, X_test_raw, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
    "    X, y, test_size=0.20, random_state=42, stratify=y\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "scaler  = StandardScaler()\n",
    "X_train = pd.DataFrame(scaler.fit_transform(X_train_raw), columns=X.columns)\n",
    "X_test  = pd.DataFrame(scaler.transform(X_test_raw),      columns=X.columns)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Training samples : {X_train.shape[0]}')\n",
    "print(f'Testing  samples : {X_test.shape[0]}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b97bf8c3-ce91-4ce7-a097-bb657f28648e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Train/test split divides the data into two parts — 80% for training the model and 20% for testing it on unseen data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "8187b133-b3a1-4be3-85be-efd42682a390",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Model trained!\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "#train the model\n",
    "lr_model = LogisticRegression(C=1.0, solver='lbfgs', max_iter=1000, random_state=42)\n",
    "lr_model.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Model trained!')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "778d7719-fb2f-4c92-80d4-448cedaac51f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#predictions\n",
    "lr_pred       = lr_model.predict(X_test)\n",
    "lr_pred_proba = lr_model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "9effa2d1-250d-491e-be01-80c442ed9a63",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Accuracy  : 0.8683\n",
      "Precision : 0.8482\n",
      "Recall    : 0.9048\n",
      "F1-Score  : 0.8756\n",
      "AUC-ROC   : 0.9440\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "#evaluation matrics\n",
    "\n",
    "lr_accuracy  = accuracy_score(y_test,  lr_pred)\n",
    "lr_precision = precision_score(y_test, lr_pred)\n",
    "lr_recall    = recall_score(y_test,    lr_pred)\n",
    "lr_f1        = f1_score(y_test,        lr_pred)\n",
    "lr_auc       = roc_auc_score(y_test,   lr_pred_proba)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Accuracy  : {lr_accuracy:.4f}')\n",
    "print(f'Precision : {lr_precision:.4f}')\n",
    "print(f'Recall    : {lr_recall:.4f}')\n",
    "print(f'F1-Score  : {lr_f1:.4f}')\n",
    "print(f'AUC-ROC   : {lr_auc:.4f}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "1c3b52f9-5b50-4000-a7ef-12b2fdb4c0ef",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "              precision    recall  f1-score   support\n",
      "\n",
      "  No Disease       0.89      0.83      0.86       100\n",
      "     Disease       0.85      0.90      0.88       105\n",
      "\n",
      "    accuracy                           0.87       205\n",
      "   macro avg       0.87      0.87      0.87       205\n",
      "weighted avg       0.87      0.87      0.87       205\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "#classification_report\n",
    "print(classification_report(y_test, lr_pred, target_names=['No Disease', 'Disease']))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "id": "b1706bb6-39e5-4c6f-a9a1-f58eb82ccc1a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
